        <tag name="ignores armor">Don't subtract armor from the damage taken.</tag>
        <tag name="messy">It does damage in a particularly destructive way, ripping people and things apart.</tag>
        <tag name="piercing">It goes right through armor. When you deal damage with n piercing, you subtract n from the enemy's armor for that attack.</tag>
        <tag name="precise">It rewards careful strikes. You use DEX to hack and slash with this weapon, not STR.</tag>
        <tag name="reload">After you attack with it, it takes more than a moment to reset for another attack.</tag>
        <tag name="stun">When you attack with it, it does stun damage instead of normal damage.</tag>
        <tag name="thrown">Throw it at someone to hurt them. If you volley with this weapon, you can't choose to mark off ammo on a 7-9; once you throw it, it's gone until you can recover it.</tag>
        <tag name="hand">It's useful for attacking something within your reach, no further.</tag>
        <tag name="close">It's useful for attacking something at arm's reach plus a foot or two.</tag>
        <tag name="reach">It's useful for attacking something that's several feet away - maybe as far as ten.</tag>
        <tag name="near">It's useful for attacking if you can see the whites of their eyes.</tag>
        <tag name="far">It's useful for attacking something in shouting distance.</tag>
        <tag name="clumsy">It's tough to move around with. -1 ongoing while using it. This penalty is cumulative.</tag>
    </tags>
